Experiment: RFC #0052 implementation based on auto_prepend_file
========================================================================
$Id$


Hello world example
-------------------
To try this out, type:

  $ php -dauto_prepend_file=xp.php Hello.class.php <Name>

Replace <Name> by anything you wish:)


Extended example
----------------
Loads an XP class and instanciates it:

  $ php -dauto_prepend_file=xp.php Instanciate.class.php <FQCN>
  
Replace <FQCN> by any XP fully qualified class name, e.g. "util.Date".
Watch what happens when you pass a non-existant class name!

<EOF>
